# game-management-models

## Core Data Models

### Game Entity
- Sport-specific configuration templates
- Location coordinates with venue metadata
- Weather condition thresholds per sport type
- Participant capacity rules and waiting lists
- Game status lifecycle (open, full, canceled, completed)

### Game-Player Relationships
- Many-to-many with role designations (host, player, waitlist)
- Participation history tracking
- Sport-specific stats collection
- Achievement unlocking based on game completion

### Weather Integration Models
- 4-hour weather window analysis for outdoor games
- Sport-specific weather condition limits:
  - Temperature ranges (40°F-95°F)
  - Precipitation thresholds
  - Wind speed maximums
- Automatic game status updates based on conditions

## Business Rules

### Game Creation
- Duplicate detection within time/location proximity
- Sport-specific validation rules for venues
- Minimum/maximum participant limits by sport type
- Required lead time for game scheduling

### Game Management
- No edits within 2 hours of start time
- No deletion within 4 hours of start time
- Games remain visible until end time + 2 hour buffer (for post-game interaction)
- Automatic database archival 7 days after game date
- Weather-based game status updates
- Location-based player recommendations

### Achievement System
- Progressive unlocking based on participation
- Sport-specific milestone tracking
- Multi-criteria award conditions
- Real-time achievement updates

